<br>
The setting: outside the Tizmak caves in the Great Divide.<br>
<br>
The targets: various Tizmaks, chiefly champions (usually yellow), furious warriors (red) and warriors (didn't get to con).  Charmed an augur or two also.<br>
<br>
First off, it's great fun to issue the /pet who command and have everyone flip when they hear &quot;AMERYGN is the leader.&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Second, looks like Tizmaks are good charm subjects.  With my mino horn equipped, I was able to successfully charm the champions with few resists at 27 with 111 CHA.  (Thanks for making those Electrum Star Ruby rings, Kaymar!)  The augurs fell victim fairly easily, as did the warriors.  The Furious warriors were very resistant, and resisted mez as well, but did a nice job of taunting them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
On to the real meat.  PREPARATION is key.  Have those hotkeys made in advance; I didn't even have the socials made yet, so my first charming effort didn't work out so well.  (Though it did keep an add from beating on us!)  I'm going to make a hotkey bank just for crowd control, personally.<br>
<br>
A thread on the EQ Diva boards yielded this social macro which I plan to make tonight:<br>
Line 1: /g %T is now my pet! %o will now assist us!<br>
Line 2: /pause 7,/assist (Main Assist) [change as needed]<br>
Line 3: /pause 7,/pet attack<br>
Line 4: /pause 120<br>
Line 5: /pet target<br>
<br>
This lets the party know you have a pet, targets whatever your main assist is fighting, sics the pet on it, then retargets the pet (leaving room for a twist of something else) for recharming.<br>
<br>
Also, I think using a view other than first-person might help.  In the swirling melees with agro shifting constantly (effectively round-robin taunting) it became hard to keep the targeting straight.  The macro may help this.<br>
<br>
Ya know, I think if done carefully, it might be possible for me to solo the ones in the front of the cave by charm kiting, especially if the second one is snared... Might also be very doable for a bard/druid combo.  If opportunity permits will try it and report back!  (Feeling froggy, Lego or Tavasilthar? )<br>
<br>
In any case, I'm going to be much better prepared tonight.<br>
<br>
